title: Susan Austin Taylor on Astral Projection - Part 2
description:
Part 2 of 2: Austin Astral Projection Meetup Group Presents - Susan Austin Taylor on Astral Projection - October 16, 2013 · 6:30 PM - INACS Home Office, Austin TX

Susan will explain what she uses Astral Projection for at this time and is going to reveal some things you can do out of body that you won't find in books.  These are things she was taught, by her non-physical companions, during her astral apprenticeship.  Good stuff!

Susan Austin Taylor is a metaphysical teacher and psychic medium living in the state of Texas.  Astral travel is her passion; she began exploring the astral realms at an early age.  After being approached by her guides and teachers in spirit, she began an apprenticeship with them lasting several years. Under their guidance she became more proficient and effective as an astral volunteer, eventually becoming an intermediary to the  dead and dying, both in this realm and in the astral realm.  She has a unique and joyful understanding of the process of dying, which is freely shared in all of her work.

Susan is also a writer and poet whose works have appeared in various magazines and journals.  She has been a regular guest on the radio talk show Dick Sutphen’s Metaphysical World for the past several years and has been a featured speaker and instructor at the Ozark Research Institute. She is currently working on a manuscript about her experiences out of the body and is available for workshops and speaking engagements.

http://susanaustintaylor.com/
